description: Bentley Motors Limited is a British designer, manufacturer and marketer of luxury cars and SUVs.
Rolls-Royce Motor Cars Limited is a British luxury automobile maker which is the exclusive manufacturer of Rolls-Royce-branded motor cars.
Maybach is a German luxury car brand that exists today as a part of Mercedes-Benz.
Lagonda is a British luxury car brand established in 1906, which has been owned by Aston Martin since 1947.
Bugatti Automobiles S.A.S is a French luxury automobile manufacturer and luxury brand for hyper sports cars.
Koenigsegg Automotive AB is a Swedish manufacturer of high-performance sports cars based in Ängelholm, Skåne County, Sweden.
SSC North America is an American automobile manufacturer founded in 1999 by owner Jerod Shelby and specializes in the production of sports cars.
Porsche, is a German automobile manufacturer specializing in high-performance sports cars, SUVs and sedans.
Ferrari S.p.A. is an Italian luxury sports car manufacturer based in Maranello, Italy.
Maserati S.p.A. is an Italian luxury vehicle manufacturer. Established on 1 December 1914, in Bologna, Italy.
Aston Martin Lagonda Global Holdings PLC is an English manufacturer of luxury sports cars and grand tourers.
Alfa Romeo Automobiles S.p.A. is an Italian luxury car manufacturer and a subsidiary of Stellantis.
Lamborghini S.p.A. is an Italian brand and manufacturer of luxury sports cars and SUVs based in Sant'Agata Bolognese.
McLaren Automotive is a British luxury automotive manufacturer based at the McLaren Technology Centre in Woking, England.
Mercedes-Benz, commonly referred to as Mercedes and sometimes as Benz, is a German luxury and commercial vehicle automotive brand.
Bayerische Motoren Werke AG, abbreviated as BMW, is a German multinational manufacturer of performance luxury vehicles and motorcycles.
The Cadillac Motor Car Division is a division of the American automobile manufacturer General Motors that designs and builds luxury vehicles.
Lexus is the luxury vehicle division of the Japanese automaker Toyota. Lexus is Japan's largest-selling make of premium cars.
Audi AG Aktiengesellschaft, commonly referred to as Audi, is a German automotive manufacturer of luxury vehicles headquartered in Ingolstadt, Bavaria.
Volvo Cars is a Swedish multinational manufacturer of luxury vehicles headquartered in Torslanda, Gothenburg.
Jaguar is the luxury vehicle brand of Jaguar Land Rover, a British multinational car manufacturer with its headquarters in Whitley, Coventry, England.
Lincoln Motor Company, or simply Lincoln, is the luxury vehicle division of American automobile manufacturer Ford.
Land Rover is a British brand of predominantly four-wheel drive, off-road capable vehicles, owned by multinational car manufacturer Jaguar Land Rover.
Tesla, Inc. is an American multinational automotive electric vehicle brand.
Stellantis North America is one of the Big Three automobile manufacturers in the United States, headquartered in Auburn Hills, Michigan.
Pontiac or formally the Pontiac Motor Division of General Motors, was an American automobile brand owned, manufactured, and commercialized by General Motors.
Infiniti is the luxury vehicle division of the Japanese automaker Nissan.
Mini is a British automotive marque founded in 1969, owned by German automotive company BMW since 2000, and used by them for a range of small cars.
Genesis Motor, LLC, commonly referred to as Genesis, is the luxury vehicle division of the South Korean vehicle manufacturer Hyundai Motor Company.
Ford Motor Company is an American multinational automobile manufacturer headquartered in Dearborn, Michigan, United States.
